Weak is a version of Rc that holds a non-owning reference to the managed value. The value is accessed by calling upgrade on the Weak pointer.
Constructs a new Weak<T> without allocating any memory. Calling upgrade on the return value always gives None.
Attempts to upgrade the Weak pointer to an Rc, extending the lifetime of the value if successful. Returns None if the value has since been dropped.
add_triples: Weak is a version of Rc that holds a non-owning reference to the managed value. The value is accessed by calling upgrade on the Weak pointer, which returns an Option<Rc<T>>. Since a Weak reference does not count towards ownership, it will not prevent the inner value from being dropped, and Weak itself makes no guarantees about the value still being present and may return None when upgraded.
Constructs a new Weak<T> without allocating any memory. Calling [upgrade][Weak::upgrade] on the return value always gives [None].
Attempts to upgrade the Weak pointer to an Rc, extending the lifetime of the value if successful. Returns [None] if the value has since been dropped.
